  • Computer Science
GPT-4, a large-scale, multimodal model which can accept image and text inputs and produce text outputs, is developed, a Transformer-based model pre-trained to predict the next token in a document which exhibits human-level performance on various professional and academic benchmarks.

    Bang YangAsif RazaYuexian ZouTong Zhang
    Computer Science, Medicine
    ArXiv
  • 2023
This work proposes customizing off-the-shelf general-purpose large-scale pre-trained models, i.e., foundation models (FMs), in computer vision and natural language processing with a specific focus on medical report generation and demonstrates that unfreezing EVA-ViT-g to learn medical image representations, followed by parameter-efficient training of ChatGLM-6B to capture the writing styles of medical reports, is essential for achieving optimal results.
